          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Provenance -->
    <section id="provenance" class="concept-block concept-block--reverse">
      <div class="concept-block__text k-prose-content">
        <h2>Provenance & signing</h2>
        <p>
          Every write — learn, update, retract, subsume, sync — is a commit
          authored under an identity-carrying address. Agent commits use
          <code>&lt;agent-id&gt;+&lt;operation&gt;@agents.knomit.io</code> as the
          author; humans use their own email with <code>+operation</code>
          subaddressing. Commits are signed with the agent's Ed25519 key.
        </p>
        <p>
          That makes the <strong>(who, what, when, why)</strong> tuple
          cryptographic rather than hand-waved. The same key that signs commits
          also names the branch and authenticates remote sync — one identity,
          end to end.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="concept-block__art">
        <div class="prov-card k-mono" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="prov-row"><span class="prov-k">commit</span> <span class="prov-v prov-v--green">9e4b2f1</span></div>
