          </div>
          <div class="uri-divider"></div>
          <div class="uri-row">
            <span class="uri-type">fact</span>
            <div class="uri-text"><span class="uri-scheme">knomit:</span><span class="uri-host">/kb/technology/security/ai/</span><span class="uri-path">c7fbe083.md</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="uri-divider"></div>
          <div class="uri-row">
            <span class="uri-type">web</span>
            <div class="uri-text"><span class="uri-scheme">https://</span><span class="uri-host">kpmg.com/us/en/home/media/</span><span class="uri-path">press-releases/2026/06/ai-agents.html</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="uri-divider"></div>
          <div class="uri-row">
            <span class="uri-type">commit</span>
            <div class="uri-text"><span class="uri-scheme">knomit-kb@</span><span class="uri-host">trunk/</span><span class="uri-path">124c68ec · 2026-06-26</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <!-- Synthesis & hypotheses -->
    <section id="synthesis" class="concept-block concept-block--reverse">
      <div class="concept-block__text k-prose-content">
        <h2>Synthesis &amp; hypotheses</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Review</strong> (<code>knomit_review</code>) is a
          session-based maintenance loop with three passes: <em>prune</em> —
          remove redundant or stale facts; <em>distill</em> — cluster related
          facts and derive a <code>synthesis</code> fact (a higher-order claim
          that no individual source fact makes on its own); <em>reflect</em> —
          record <code>methodology</code> facts from resolved hypothesis
          transitions. Synthesis produces new knowledge from what the corpus
          already holds.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Hypothesize</strong> (<code>knomit_hypothesize</code>) is a
          separate, explicit pass over synthesis facts. For each one it decides
          whether a <code>hypothesis</code> is warranted — a falsifiable,
          forward-looking prediction with a concrete settlement criterion.
          <strong>Skipping is the expected default</strong>; a hypothesis is
          only written when it fills a genuinely load-bearing gap that new
          evidence could close.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="concept-block__art">
        <div class="synth-card" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="synth-phase">
            <span class="synth-tool k-mono">knomit_review · distill</span>
            <div class="synth-items">
              <span class="synth-item k-mono">◉ KPMG: 68% employees use AI agents</span>
              <span class="synth-item k-mono">◉ OpenAI Codex: 85% of output tokens</span>
              <span class="synth-item k-mono">◉ Anthropic: Claude writes ~80% of code</span>
            </div>
            <span class="synth-arrow">↓</span>
            <span class="synth-output k-mono">◆ Mid-2026: AI agents move from experimental to primary</span>
          </div>
          <div class="synth-divider"></div>
          <div class="synth-phase">
            <span class="synth-tool k-mono">knomit_hypothesize · selectively</span>
            <span class="synth-input k-mono">◆ Mid-2026: AI agents move from experimental…</span>
            <span class="synth-arrow">↓</span>
            <span class="synth-output synth-output--hyp k-mono">? Agent-led orgs outperform by 2× — Q4 2027</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MCP loop -->
    <section id="mcp" class="concept-block">
      <div class="concept-block__text k-prose-content">
        <h2>The MCP operational loop</h2>
        <p>
          MCP is not an optional add-on — it is the primary interface for
          humans (via Claude Code and editors) and agents alike. Seven tools
          cover the full fact lifecycle; their descriptions carry all the
          behavioral guidance a model needs, with no prompt scaffolding required.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each agent connects to a <strong>branch-scoped endpoint</strong>, so
          reads and writes land on its own branch automatically — isolation is
          structural, not enforced by convention. Three profiles
          (<code>code</code>, <code>chat</code>, <code>generic</code>) tailor
          the tool descriptions to the kind of client connecting.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="concept-block__art">
        <div class="mcp-card" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="mcp-row">
            <span class="mcp-phase k-mono">recall</span>
            <span class="mcp-tool k-mono">knomit_query</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mcp-row">
            <span class="mcp-phase k-mono">write</span>
            <span class="mcp-tool k-mono">knomit_learn</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mcp-row">
            <span class="mcp-phase k-mono">trace</span>
            <span class="mcp-tool k-mono">knomit_explain</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mcp-row">
            <span class="mcp-phase k-mono">revise</span>
            <span class="mcp-tool k-mono">knomit_update · knomit_retract</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mcp-row">
            <span class="mcp-phase k-mono">synthesize</span>
            <span class="mcp-tool k-mono">knomit_review</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mcp-row mcp-row--last">
            <span class="mcp-phase k-mono">extend</span>
            <span class="mcp-tool k-mono">knomit_hypothesize</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

